ear to", "take precedence over the properties in the base class. To avoid", "that, we copy the properties into the derived class type itself", "via a meta class. In that way the properties will always take", "precedence."]}, {"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMethods.__module__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMethods.__doc__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMethods.__doc__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMethods.__dict__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["We similar use a property for __dict__. We need __dict__ to be", "explicit to ensure that vars() works as expected."]}, {"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMethods.__weakref__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Need to also propagate the special __weakref__ attribute for case", "where decorating classes which will define this. If do not define", "it and use a function like inspect.getmembers() on a decorator", "class it will fail. This can't be in the derived classes."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMetaType", "bases": ["type"], "methods": [{"name": "async_property.proxy._ObjectProxyMetaType.__new__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": nul